umber	731 CONT Line	41 CONT Roll	CSSCT1901_2961 CONT1 CONT Name	William Mchugh1 CONT Age	581 CONT Estimated Birth Year	abt 18431 CONT Relationship	Head1 CONT Spouse's Name	Bridget H Hugh1 CONT Gender	Male1 CONT Where born	Ireland1 CONT Registration Number	644/81 CONT Registration district	Milton1 CONT Civil parish	Glasgow Milton1 CONT County	Lanarkshire1 CONT Address	12 (backland) William St1 CONT Occupation	Coporation Labourer1 CONT1 CONT Name	Bridget H Hugh1 CONT Age	561 CONT Estimated Birth Year	abt 18451 CONT Relationship	Wife1 CONT Spouse's Name	William Mchugh1 CONT Gender	Female1 CONT Where born	Ireland1 CONT Registration Number	644/81 CONT Registration district	Milton1 CONT Civil parish	Glasgow Milton1 CONT County	Lanarkshire1 CONT Address	12 (backland) William St1 CONT1 CONT Name	Bridget H Hugh1 CONT [Bridget H Mchugh]1 CONT Age	201 CONT Estimated Birth Year	abt 18811 CONT Relationship	Daur (Daughter)1 CONT Father's Name	William Mchugh1 CONT Mother's Name	Bridget H Hugh1 CONT Gender	Female1 CONT Where born	Glasgow, Lanarkshire1 CONT Registration Number	644/81 CONT Registration district	Milton1 CONT Civil parish	Glasgow Milton1 CONT County	Lanarkshire1 CONT Address	12 (backland) William St1 CHAN2 DATE 16 AUG 20243 TIME 10:16:291 _CRE2 DATE 16 AUG 20243 TIME 10:12:520 @11544911@ NOTE1 CONT Terry Blyth1 CONT1 CONT Burrial: 1 CONT Scoonie Cemetery, Leven1 CHAN2 DATE 17 AUG 20243 TIME 12:12:491 _CRE2 DATE 11 MAR 20223 TIME 16:39:310 @3659096@ NOTE1 CONT Terry Blyth1 CONT1 CONT 22 Dec 19691 CONT 40 Casan, Leven, Fife1 CONT terminal broncho pneumonia; congestive cardiac failure1 CHAN2 DATE 17 AUG 20243 TIME 12:12:401 _CRE2 DATE 11 MAR 20223 TIME 16:38:430 @88537170@ NOTE1 CONT https://www.ancestry.co.uk/mediaui-viewer/collection/1030/tree/25721947/person/1701513041/media/28cf43c2-9427-4eea-bd27-ce2c1254a6b9?galleryindex=21&sort=-created1 CONT accessed 11 Mar 20221 CONT1 CONT My Granny - by Terry Blyth, March 20111 CONT1 CONT1 CONT Discovered after her death that her real name was Agnes Weir, father Ninian Weir. 'Parents shown on marriage cert wrong. Not known why.1 CONT Known all life as Jessie Moonie nee McCue1 CONT Parish relief claim finally traced at Mitchell Library which helps to unravel mystery.1 CONT1 CONT In April 1908 at aged nearly 14, she was found destitute by the police in a stairwell in William Street, Milton, 'in a very filthy condition' Mother was said to be cohabiting with William Elliott, although he is said to be residing with his sister Mrs McG1 CONC arry at North Oswald St. Mother said to reside at Phoenix Park Terrace and working under the name of Jessie Smith at Star Home. She is shown as having 3 children to William Elliott. Father shown as Ninian Weir but current whereabouts unknown. Jessie is sh1 CONC own to have previously been kept by friends. She had been before the court on 9/4/1908 and remanded for 24 hours. She was brought before the court again on 10/4/1908 and was put to Stobhill Hospital on that day. Report shows she was kept for some years by1 CONC  Mrs McHugh of 15 William Street, Milton.1 CONT1 CONT Jessie was then traced on the 1901 census with William and Bridget McHugh, shown as Jessie McHugh aged 7 at 12 William Street, Milton, Glasgow. William was 58 and Bridget was 56. Also in the house was their daughter Bridget aged 20. Next door was also the1 CONC  O'Rourkes with whom Jessie is shown as staying with at some time (on parish relief claim). Also in the same close is Elizabeth Winter and her family - this is Elizabeth McHugh daughter of William and Bridget. Also in the same close is Mary McGee who is a1 CONC nother daughter of William and Bridget!1 CONT1 CONT I think the reason that Jessie was destitute and out of the house in April 08 was the fact that Bridget McHugh died aged 64 in January 08, William would have ben 68, quite elderly in those days, his daughter Bridget if she was still in the house, suffered1 CONC  from heart disease, dying 11 months later (she had a different home address then). This could have been a difficult situation for Jessie.1 CONT1 CONT In August 08, Jessie leaves the poorhouse and goes to stay with a Mrs Winter at 12 William St - this will be Elizabeth McHugh. She is destitute again from 12 William Street, in Jan 09 and stays in poorhouse until Sept 09 when she goes to stay with 'friend1 CONC s' again - is this Elizabeth Winter again? in Oct 09, she is again destitute from 12 William Street, and is put to work in Glasgow. There is no further mention of Winter or McHugh but William McHugh didn't die until 1923. However research shows that Eliza1 CONC beth Winter and her family move to Lochee - her chldren marry from a Lochee address from 1918. Jessie makes poor relief claims until Dec 1911 when she leaves Barnhill - does she go to Elizabeth in Dundee - is this how she meets Michael Moonie?? (She stays1 CONC  for a while in 1911 with the O'Rourkes in 12 William Street) At the time of initial claim in 1908, her mother was living 5 minutes away in Phoenix Park Terrace!1 CONT1 CONT The family have always thought that Grannie Moonie was brought up by grandparents and that she was an orphan. It was always thought that her name was Jessie McCue - in fact on her own marriage cert she is shown as Jessie McCue with parents as William McCu1 CONC e and Mary McCue nee Winter.  She has obviously used a combination of names. She never spoke about her family, the thought being, she was too young to know what happened. Sad to think she did know but chose not to tell. All her life she was a cheery sole,1 CONC  her life given up to care for her big family....  1 CONT Reg'd grandson, Joseph, illegitimate son of Cathie, death in 1943, was at 16 Kirkland Gardens1 CONT1 CONT Her death cert seen at GROS. Died at daughter Tommy's home. Died aged 75 of terminal broncho pneumonia; congestive cardiac failure. Death reg'd by son Michael1 CONT1 CONT  1 CONT1 CONT Further update:1 CONT1 CONT Jessie stayed with William and Bridget McHugh possibly 1901-1908.1 CONT1 CONT William's brother James McHugh married Mary Jane Mulligan. Their daughter Roseann b1895 married Thomas Howe. Their son James Howe married Rebecca O'Hara (daughter Sharon Howe) Rebecca qas the grandaughter of Matthew Weir and Mary Ann Kane. Matthew Weir wa1 CONC s Ninian Weir's brother. There must therefore have been a connection with Jessie going to stay with the McHugh's in 19011 CHAN2 DATE 16 AUG 20243 TIME 09:35:521 _CRE2 DATE 11 MAR 20223 TIME 16:53:250 @11205814@ NOTE1 CONT Born1 CONT 20 June 18941 CONT 13 McAdam's Lane, Glasgow1 CHAN2 DATE 11 MAR 20223 TIME 16:53:241 _CRE2 DATE 25 FEB 20223 TIME 19:13:190 @93234802@ NOTE1 CONT 1891 census1 CONT1 CHAN2 DATE 06 MAR 20223 TIME 13:54:311 _CRE2 DATE 06 MAR 20223 TIME 13:54:200 @86782682@ NOTE1 CONT MOONEY1 CONT MICHAEL1 CONT 641 CONT KELLY1 CONT 18751 CONT 282/5 971 CONT Lochee1 CHAN2 DATE 07 MAR 20223 TIME 19:00:551 _CRE2 DATE 07 MAR 20223 TIME 19:00:480 @97383200@ NOTE1 CONT https://www.findagrave.com/memorial/127257165/michael-mooney1 CONT1 CONT Michael Mooney1 CONT BIRTH1 CONT 17981 CONT County Cavan, Ireland1 CONT DEATH1 CONT 23 Mar 1875 (aged 76–77)1 CONT BURIAL1 CONT Liff And Benvie Churchyards1 CONT Liff, Angus, Scotland  Show Map1 CONT MEMORIAL ID1 CONT 127257165 · View Source1 CONT1 CONT 25 March - Buried1 CONT Occupation: Jute Mill Worker1 CONT Widower of Annie Herrington1 CONT Resided at 130 Liff Road, Lochee1 CONT Died aged 64 years1 CONT Father: Thomas Mooney, Farm Labourer *Deceased)1 CONT Mother: Bridget Mooney nee Kelly Deceased1 CONT Cause of Death : Paralysis for 3 years, Bronchitis 7 days.1 CONT Reported by Agnes Mooney1 CHAN2 DATE 29 JUN 20233 TIME 18:41:071 _CRE2 DATE 29 JUN 20233 TIME 18:40:310 @38550142@ NOTE1 CONT Death Certificate 971 CONT1 CONT Michael Mooney, formerly Jute Millwo