 CONT Surname    Mooney or Moonie1 CONT Prenames    Thomas1 CONT Age    6yrs 2mths1 CONT Address    Paton Land, Liff Rd, Lochee1 CONT Occupation1 CONT Birthplace    Patons' Land, Liff Rd, Lochee1 CONT Disabled    Wholly1 CONT Marital Status1 CONT Dependents1 CONT Admit Reason    His mothers death1 CONT Admit Date    2 June 18631 CONT Admit No    18151 CONT AdmitNoSearch    18151 CONT Disch Date1 CONT Disch Reason1 CONT Notes1 CONT1 CONT Notes from the archivist:1 CONT Thomas Mooney was entered on to the poor roll for the Liff and Benvie parish, which covered most of the West side of the town. This does not necessarily mean that he was admitted to the poorhouse, but rather that he was admitted on to the poor roll. This 1 CONC means that the parish board was giving out money to support him, which implies that he was still living at home in Paton’s Land. - email dated 28 Oct 20211 CONT1 CHAN2 DATE 04 MAR 20223 TIME 17:32:271 _CRE2 DATE 04 MAR 20223 TIME 17:14:130 @92902944@ NOTE1 CONT ....The Sheriff after hearing corroborative evidence, found the charge proved, and ordered prisoner to find caution of 30s to keep the peace for six months, or go prison lor twenty days. His Lordship remarked that if the knile had been sharp enough prison1 CONC er might have killed his wife.1 CONT1 CONT Published: Friday 20 December 18951 CONT Newspaper: Dundee Evening Telegraph1 CONT County: Angus, Scotland1 CONT Type: Article | Words: 133 | Page: 4 | Tags: none1 CONT1 CHAN2 DATE 20 FEB 20223 TIME 23:59:011 _CRE2 DATE 20 FEB 20223 TIME 23:58:550 @90265952@ NOTE1 CONT Did he go to prison - look on Scotlandspeople1 CONT https://www.scotlandspeople.gov.uk/record-results?search_type=people&dl_cat=prison&surname=mooney&surname_so=exact&forename=thomas&forename_so=starts&sex=M&from_year=1895&country_of_birth%5B0%5D=SCOTLAND&trial_court_so=starts&record_type=prison_records1 CONT1 CONT Reference	HH002100047-00006-1 CONT Forename	THOMAS1 CONT Surname	MOONEY1 CONT Second surname	-----1 CONT Gender	M1 CONT Age	381 CONT Has alias name(s)	-----1 CONT Country of birth	SCOTLAND1 CONT Where born	LOCHEE1 CONT Year admitted	18951 CONT Prison	PERTH PRISON1 CONT Trial court	SHERIFF COURT DUNDEE1 CHAN2 DATE 05 MAR 20223 TIME 13:06:051 _CRE2 DATE 05 MAR 20223 TIME 13:04:430 @44315724@ NOTE1 CONT Threatening to Cut His Wipe's Throat.— A labourer named Thomas Mooney, residing in Albert Street, Lochee, was charged before Sheriff Campbell Smith in Dundee Sheriff Court yester- day with wife assault. He pleaded not guilty. Mrs Mooney stated that she ha1 CONC d been married sixteen years, and had had eleven of a family, seven of whom were alive. On Saturday, 14th inst., her husband came home the worse for drink. Sbe was in bed when he seized her by the hair of the of the head, pulled her upon the floor, and, r1 CONC emarking that he would cut her throat, he lifted a knife from the table and drew it twice acrces her neck, inflicting slight injuries. The accused also beat his wife with his fists, and knocked her down.1 CONT1 CONT Published: Saturday 21 December 18951 CONT Newspaper: Dundee Courier1 CONT County: Angus, Scotland1 CONT Type: Article | Words: 3234 | Page: 2 | Tags: none1 CONT1 CHAN2 DATE 20 FEB 20223 TIME 23:59:441 _CRE2 DATE 20 FEB 20223 TIME 23:59:060 @90411020@ NOTE1 CONT Scotlandsprople.gov.uk Deaths	MOONEY	HANNAH1 CONT Age	301 CONT Mother	HARRINGTON1 CONT Date	18631 CONT Fer	282/3 331 CONT Place	Dundee Third District1 CONT EstDoB	18331 CHAN2 DATE 07 FEB 20223 TIME 23:08:221 _CRE2 DATE 07 FEB 20223 TIME 23:08:210 @8271368@ NOTE1 CONT 18331 CONT Bailieborough, Cavan, Ireland1 CHAN2 DATE 09 MAR 20223 TIME 15:46:031 _CRE2 DATE 09 MAR 20223 TIME 15:45:480 @18904212@ NOTE1 CONT <ref>1 CONT '''Baptism''':1 CONT "Scotland, Select Births and Baptisms, 1564-1950"<br/>1 CONT Original data: Scotland, Births and Baptisms, 1564-1950. Salt Lake City, Utah: FamilySearch, 