pril 12 at Leven1 CHAN2 DATE 12 MAR 20223 TIME 17:18:511 _CRE2 DATE 12 MAR 20223 TIME 17:10:570 @20244604@ NOTE1 CONT Name:	William Campbell1 CONT Gender:	Male1 CONT Birth Date:	30 Oct 18581 CONT Birth Place:	Stirling,Stirling,Scotland1 CONT Father:	1 CONT James Campbell1 CONT Mother:	1 CONT Janet Mc Vey1 CONT1 CHAN2 DATE 12 APR 20223 TIME 09:33:311 _CRE2 DATE 12 APR 20223 TIME 09:22:090 @79014120@ NOTE1 CONT A son's visit to his mother1 CONT1 CONT Exciting scene in Scouringburn1 CONT In Dundee Police Court - Bailie Belville on the bench - William Stevenson described as a labourer and Ann McIntee or Butler were charged with assaulting Hannah Mooney or Stevensonand James Eason, Carter, Dempster Street. Stevenson was further accused of l1 CONC icking Constable William Begg. From the statement submitted by the Prosceutor ir appeared that Mrs Stevenson was William's mother. Since July she had not seen him until Saturday evening when he called at her house in Dempster Street and demanded a silver 1 CONC medal which he had won for swimming. Her sister was searching for it when James Easson, who cohabited with Mrs Stevenson arrived on the scene. Without warning William rushed at him, and struck him several blows on the face, siezed hold of the muffler the 1 CONC was wearing, and nearly choked him. Mrs Butler who was apparently in waiting outside, then dashed into the house, and kicked Eason about the face and body. In the uproar Mrs  Stevenson also received a blow to the head, and so outrageous did her son become1 CONC  that she went to the door and shouted for the police. He followed and was met by two officers who took him into custody. He resented this interferance, and lay down on the street and resisted. In his struggles he kicked Constable Begg. Stevenson was sent1 CONC  to prison for a month and Butler for twenty days.1 CHAN2 DATE 16 APR 20223 TIME 12:19:051 _CRE2 DATE 16 APR 20223 TIME 12:05:080 @42071664@ NOTE1 CONT page 67 