nown grave but is remembered on the Thiepval Memorial.1 CONT1 CONT1 CONT Joseph Lynch   240343   Black Watch1 CONT1 CONT News has been received by Mrs Lynch, 20 Pole Street, Dundee, that her son, Private Joseph Lynch, Black Watch, was killed in action on the 23rd October.  Private Lynch enlisted in February 1914, and went to the front in October 1914.  Prior to joining the 1 CONC colours, he was a millworker.  He was 21 years of age.1 CONT1 CONT1 CONT LYNCH___Killed in action, on 23rd October, 1916, 1876 Private Joseph Lynch, signaller, Headquarters, Black Watch.  B.E.F.  – Inserted by his sorrowing father and mother and family.  Mr and Mrs Edward Lynch, 20 Pole Street, Polepark Road, Dundee.1 CONT1 CONT Dundee People’s Journal 11th November 19161 CHAN2 DATE 04 MAR 20223 TIME 18:16:471 _CRE2 DATE 04 MAR 20223 TIME 18:16:200 @84363484@ NOTE1 CONT Fold3.com1 CONT1 CONT Dependants pension1 CONT1 CONT Name  Lynch Joseoh1 CONT Regimental No  2403431 CONT Regiment  Royal Highlanders1 CONT Rank  Private1 CONT Date received from paymaster  20-6-171 CONT Date and cause of death  Missing BEF, 23-10-161 CONT Dependant  Mrs Mary Lynch1 CONT Address  20 Pole St, Polepark Road, Dundee1 CONT Relationship  Mother1 CONT Pension Eight AShillings  1 CONT Date awarded  21-7-171 CONT1 CHAN2 DATE 15 AUG 20243 TIME 16:08:301 _CRE2 DATE 04 MAR 20223 TIME 18:17:370 @53626679@ NOTE1 CONT <ref>1 CONT '''Memorial''':1 CONT "UK, Commonwealth War Graves, 1914-1921 and 1939-1947"<br/>1 CONT Commonwealth War Graves Commission; Author: Peter Singlehurst; Series Title: British Commonwealth War Graves Registers, 1914-1918; Archive Name: London, United Kingdom<br/>1 CONT {{Ancestry Record|2706|561061|uk}} (accessed 15 August 2024)<br/>1 CONT Name: Joseph Lynch; Gender: Male; Age: 21; Birth Date: abt 1895; Death Date: 23 Oct 1916; Cemetery: The Thiepval Memorial; Burial Country: France; Regiment: Black Watch (Royal Highlanders); Regimental Number: 240343; 