arriage certificate details1 CONT Posted 14 Aug 2012 by TerryBlyth1 CONT  Married in 1915 as Jessie McCue, aged 20, a flax millworker, (would have been 21) of 11 North Street, Leven. Witnesses were William William Wood and Mary Jane Lynch. 1 CONT1 CONT  1 CONT1 CONT Father shown as William McCue (this would be William McHugh  who she stayed with when she was young - he was shown as deceased but he didn't die until 1923). Her mother was shown as Mary McCue MS Winter. (There was a Mary McHugh who was William's oldest d1 CONC aughter and Winter was Elizabeth McHugh's married name. Jessie stayed with her frequently in Glasgow in between spells in Poorhouse). I also think she followed her to Dundee, where she would possibly  have met Michael.1 CHAN2 DATE 16 AUG 20243 TIME 10:26:121 _CRE2 DATE 16 AUG 20243 TIME 10:18:380 @98478848@ NOTE1 CONT Marriagge Cert Notes by Terry Blyth Aug 20121 CONT1 CONT Married in 1915 as Jessie McCue, aged 20, a flax millworker, (would have been 21) of 11 North Street, Leven. Witnesses were William William Wood and Mary Jane Lynch. 1 CONT1 CONT  1 CONT1 CONT Father shown as William McCue (this would be William McHugh  who she stayed with when she was young - he was shown as deceased but he didn't die until 1923). Her mother was shown as Mary McCue MS Winter. (There was a Mary McHugh who was William's oldest d1 CONC aughter and Winter was Elizabeth McHugh's married name. Jessie stayed with her frequently in Glasgow in between spells in Poorhouse). I also think she followed her to Dundee, where she would possibly  have met Michael.1 CHAN2 DATE 11 MAR 20223 TIME 16:58:071 _CRE2 DATE 11 MAR 20223 TIME 16:57:350 @91415496@ NOTE1 CONT page 39  line 771 CONT1 CONT 1915 Marriage in the district of Auckland in the county of Fife1 CONT1 CONT 1915 Twentyninth October at Crossroads, Methhill1 CONT1 CONT After publication according to the forms of the Roman Catholic Church1 CONT1 CONT Signed Michael Moonie, Coalminer 